==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Speckled
<hw>Spec"kled</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Marked or variegated
with small spots of a different color from that of the rest of the
surface.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Speckled Indians</b></col> <fld>(Ethnol.)</fld>, <cd>the
Pintos.</cd> -- <col><b>Speckled trout</b></col>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <cd>The common American brook trout. See
<er>Trout</er>.</cd> <sd>(b)</sd> <cd>The rainbow trout.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Speckled-belly</ent>⟦br⟧
